title: For Sale/Trade:  Price reduced -- Smith and Wesson Pocket Pistol, Model 2
postcontent: Smith and Wesson Pocket Pistol, Model 2, with mother of pearl grips and outstanding finish.  This pistol is in .38 Smith and Wesson caliber and was made in 1881 or 1882.  From what I've seen of antique rating, it is an Excellent Plus -- with only a blemish in the nickle finish on one spot on the cylinder and one on the back of the grip frame, plus a little freckling at the hinge.  The bore SHINES and the bluing on the trigger guard is perfect.  The pistol is very tight, locks up better than any modern revolver that I have ever seen, and has a very close cylinder to frame gap -- with virtually NO end play in the cylinder or side play in the hinge.  It looks and feels like a pistol that has lain in a drawer for most, if not all, of its 130-plus years.  I shot it a few times to verify that the firing mechanism works -- which it does -- and every part of the pistol works perfectly, including the double-action, single-action, and the ejection mechanism.  It is a real collector's gem.

title: For Sale:  Colt Model 1911 A1 Civilian Pre Series "70" In Rare Factory Nickel Finish
postcontent: This is a .45 A.C.P. chambered Colt 1911 pistol.  This is one of the last "C" suffix serial numbered pistols before the series "70" came out.  In the Pre Series of 1911's, there were les than 2% of these pistols that were factory nickel finished.  That makes the factory finished pistols very difficult to find.  This Colt has a Colt Factory Historical letter that cinfirms the nuckel finish and that it was originally shipped to the Johnson Plantation Gun Shop in Ashburn, Georgia on July 9, 1970.  The pistol itself shows little handling or indication of being fired.  The high polish sides have a mirror finish that I am told would rate a 99% condition.  Similarly, I have been told the top of the side and frame sides would rate a 98% condition.  The barrel shows no plating loss/wear.  The very nbice reproduction box has the corret end label with the correct Nickel Finish tag.  This is one of the nicest condition older Colt 1911's I have seen.  Any Colt collector should be happy to add this to their collection!Please FEEL FREETO MAKE AN OFFER!
